      "content": "To find the relative major of Eb major using the circle of fifths, you need to move down a minor third, or equivalently, up a major sixth, on the circle.  If you start at Eb, moving down a minor third brings you to C minor. The relative major of C minor is Eb major, so you've found it!  Remember, the relative major shares the same key signature and shares a relative minor.",
